n><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the Courts to: </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">break longstanding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">family </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">impasses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">restore</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> contact between children and non-resident parent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and identify</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> parents who posed risks to children. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">This input to the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Courts has largely disappeared for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">families who </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">need public support and no longer have it. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:7.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Families in public law childcare cases </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">also are at risk for losing expert clinician input</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, as it will not be available to them</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">By July 2013, a third of our </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">membership had closed or were closing their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">medicolegal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> practise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> because they were no longer financially viable. Legal Aid payment rates to expert clinicians were cut in October 2011. A further </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">defacto</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cut was made in January 2013, when the Legal Aid Agen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cy reduced the number of hours allowed for professional assessments, making it impossible to begin work on time and to prepare reports with professional integrity. The Government now has announced their intention to proceed with a further 20 percent cut in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> rates. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Even NHS Court teams have closed because they cannot afford to run professional staff for the rates on offer. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">What is being lost is the clinical expertise and experience of senior professionals who have contributed to the working of the Family Co</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">urts for many years. Medical specialists </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">help</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the Courts to identify non-accidental injuries, sometimes when they </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">re not suspected. They </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">help</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the Courts to identify cases where non-accidental injuries </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">re wrongly suspected. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">When mental health clinicians i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">dentify treatable problems, families </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">can be helped to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> remain together, reducing the risk of poor outcomes for a child growing up in care and the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">financial cost to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">society</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. Conversely, prompt mental health assessments can identify poor prognosis and high le</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">vels of risk, reducing delay for the child and reducing cost by assisting the Court in speedy resolution of these cases.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The real victims are the children and their families who are the subjects of Family Court proceedings. They will not have the benefit </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of expert clinical input to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ourts when decisions are made about their future.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Decisions made without relevant and accurate evidence risk justice being undermined for children and families who cannot afford to pay privately</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 21.3pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:7.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The residence test for ci</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">vil legal aid claimants </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">will exclude from public funding asylum-seeking families and their children, who are amongst the most troubled families that come before the Family Courts. Often, the parents in these cases do not speak English, and they need the ca</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reful attention of expert clinicians who can interview them, often through interpreters, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in a way that is sensitive to their cultural needs and to traumas they may have suffered before arriving in the UK. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:7.3pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The proposed restriction on the scope of legal ai</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">d available to prisoners </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">will make it impossible for parents who are in prison to participate in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">assessments regarding the care of their children. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I am available to discuss these matters further with you or to give evidence in person, if you wish. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">27 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>